Revision history for ddstartup

0.07 2026-05-06
    - added an explicit MIT license to the `ddstartup` skill
    - documented the MIT license in the README

0.06 2026-04-29
    - fixed startup units and launchd plists to derive Perl library paths from the installed dashboard layout
    - added support for dashboard installs that need sibling lib/perl5 paths such as ~/perl5/bin/dashboard
    - changed startup definitions to run dashboard through the detected active Perl interpreter
    - verified macOS startup logs and restart commands through the generated launch agent environment

0.05 2026-04-28
    - added native macOS launchd support beside the existing systemd backend
    - added launchctl-based setup, enable, disable, status, logs, and remove behavior for macOS
    - added activation reporting so macOS can distinguish loaded jobs from deferred session activation

0.04 2026-04-28
    - changed install-time auto-setup to skip cleanly on unsupported hosts
    - kept explicit ddstartup systemd commands strict when systemctl is unavailable

0.03 2026-04-28
    - fixed generated systemd units to preserve the active Perl runtime library path
    - made dashboard ddstartup.setup derive PERL5LIB from the running Perl @INC when the environment variable is unset

0.02 2026-04-28
    - changed ddstartup commands to print pretty table output by default
    - added -o json support across setup, enable, disable, status, logs, and remove

0.01 2026-04-28
    - created the ddstartup skill to manage systemd startup for Developer Dashboard
    - added setup, status, logs, and remove commands for systemctl and journalctl
    - verified the skill in Docker with 100% coverage
